## Why This Is Asked
This scenario tests practical container containment, SELinux policy implementation, audit trail configuration, and host isolation in a realistic data ingestion workflow.

## Key Concepts
- Podman user namespaces for UID/GID isolation
- SELinux targeted policy modules for domain confinement
- Auditd path monitoring for comprehensive file I/O tracking
- Secure bind mounts with minimal host filesystem exposure

## Code Example
```bash
# Create SELinux module
module ingest_t 1.0;

require {
    type unconfined_t;
    type var_run_t;
    type etc_t;
    type default_t;
    class file { read write open getattr };
    class dir { search read open getattr };
    class sock_file { write open };
}

# Policy rules for ingest_t domain
allow ingest_t etc_t:file { read open getattr };
allow ingest_t var_run_t:sock_file { write open };
allow ingest_t default_t:dir { search read open getattr };
allow ingest_t default_t:file { read write open getattr };
```

## Implementation Commands
```bash
# Create dedicated user
sudo useradd -r -s /bin/false ingest
sudo usermod -v 100000-199999 -w 100000-199999 ingest

# Build and load SELinux module
cat > ingest.te << 'EOF'
module ingest_t 1.0;

require {
    type unconfined_t;
    type var_run_t;
    type etc_t;
    type default_t;
    class file { read write open getattr };
    class dir { search read open getattr };
    class sock_file { write open };
}

allow ingest_t etc_t:file { read open getattr };
allow ingest_t var_run_t:sock_file { write open };
allow ingest_t default_t:dir { search read open getattr };
allow ingest_t default_t:file { read write open getattr };
EOF

checkmodule -M -m -o ingest.mod ingest.te
semodule_package -o ingest.pp -m ingest.mod
sudo semodule -i ingest.pp

# Configure audit rules
sudo auditctl -w /opt/ingest/config -p r -k ingest_config
sudo auditctl -w /srv/ingest/data -p rwxa -k ingest_data
sudo auditctl -w /var/run/ingest-proxy.sock -p w -k ingest_ipc

# Run container
podman run \
  --uidmap 0:100000:65536 \
  --gidmap 0:100000:65536 \
  -v /opt/ingest/config:/opt/ingest/config:ro \
  -v /srv/ingest/data:/srv/ingest/data:rw \
  -v /var/run/ingest-proxy.sock:/var/run/ingest-proxy.sock \
  --network=none \
  --security-opt label=type:ingest_t \
  --user 1000 \
  ingest-service:latest
```

## Why This Is Asked

